{
  "texts": [
    "The model shows remarkable precision and recall in the 'Neutral' category, with scores of 0.99 and 0.98 respectively, suggesting a decent performance in identifying non-inflammatory content, which is often the bulk of data and sets the baseline for model performance.",
    "In more nuanced categories, such as 'Provocative' and 'Offensive,' the model exhibits precision scores of 0.89 and 0.92, with recall scores of 0.93 and 0.99, indicating its effective differentiation between subtly differing sentiments.",
    "The 'Moderately Hateful' category, despite having fewer instances, also sees a high F1-score of 0.93, underlining the model's capability to discern complex emotional nuances in a text.",
    "These results collectively highlight the robustness of the FAST-RNN model in handling both clear-cut and borderline cases, ensuring that it performs reliably across a diverse range of textual sentiments.",
    "Fig. 8 Training and validation accuracy curve-FAST-RNN tent decrease in loss for both training and validation, suggests that the model is learning generalizable patterns rather than overfitting the training data."
  ]
}